# GitHub App Integration Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Allow company admins to connect their GitHub organization(s) via GitHub App installation, with persistent API access and real-time webhook ingestion.

**Architecture:** Admin initiates install via a state-protected redirect to GitHub, which calls back to our endpoint after org install. We store the installation and repo list in Postgres, generate short-lived installation tokens (cached in Redis, generated server-side from our private key), and route webhook events to a BullMQ queue for async processing.

**Tech Stack:** NestJS v11, Fastify, Knex, Redis (via existing CacheService), BullMQ (@nestjs/bullmq), @nestjs/axios (HttpService), Node.js built-in crypto (RS256 JWT), TypeScript strict

